    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
            <opener><dateline><date when="1912-09-07">Sep. 7, 1912</dateline></date>
                <salute>My dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Miss Monroe</persName>-</salute></opener>
            <p>I was very much interested in the announcement of "<title key="poetry" level="j">Poetry</title>" which you sent me the other
               day, care of "<title key="atlantic" level="j">The Atlantic.</title>"</p>
            <p>It is a most excellent undertaking, and ought to do much to foster poetry, which has a hard time
                to get itself published, now. I enclose a check <gap><desc>[for]</desc></gap> <measure type="currency" num="25">$25.00</measure> which will do as a subscription to the
                <title key="poetry" level="j">magazine</title>, and as a little more. Small though it is, I know that every little helps.</p>
            <p>I shall be very glad to send you some of my work a little later, and shall hope that it will meet
               with your approval. A volume of <title key="domeManyColouredGlass" level="m">my collected things</title> comes out <date when="1912-10">next month</date>,so I have very little on hand
               just now.</p>
            <closer>With best wishes for your success</closer> 
        </body>
    </text>
